<span id="freeTextContainer283676618154229043">We all owe a sacred debt to Stephen Hawking for his theories and contributions to physics. Approaching this book with a mild understanding of basic physics, I simply exhausted myself in his space-time, extra dimensions &quot;Nutshell&quot;. The amount of energy it took to comprehend a fraction of what I read left me in a swirling vacuum fluctuation. <br/><br/>It is an honor to have read Professor Hawking&apos;s book. I will tentatively rate three stars simply because the subject matter as presented was mind-numbing, alt</span>
  <span id="freeText283676618154229043" style="display:none">We all owe a sacred debt to Stephen Hawking for his theories and contributions to physics. Approaching this book with a mild understanding of basic physics, I simply exhausted myself in his space-time, extra dimensions "Nutshell". The amount of energy it took to comprehend a fraction of what I read left me in a swirling vacuum fluctuation. <br /><br />It is an honor to have read Professor Hawking's book. I will tentatively rate three stars simply because the subject matter as presented was mind-numbing, although rightfully this material is five stars.</span>
